args: Oh, but I am a fool! Letting my stomach\ngrowl in front of Elly, of all people?!
Clearly my own body has a few\nlessons to learn in propriety!
Elly's probably had it up to here with me.\nOh, whatever am I going to do?
...No. Don't give up yet, Julietta.\nThere's still a chance to turn this around!
It was a mistake to think of relaxation\nideas that involved crowded public spaces.
However, this is no time for regret;\nit is a time for action!
...You wish to take me somewhere?\nEr, might I ask where?
You will see when we get there. Come!
Hmm. It seems we have arrived\nat an abandoned cove.
Exactly so! I discovered this myself,\nso I don't think many people know of it.
It's quiet, and there's a lovely breeze.\nThe perfect place to take a nice walk\nand unwind, don't you think?
I suppose so. But why bring me here?
Oh, uh... So we can concentrate!
After all, a Paladyn must preserve\nher composure at all times.
I figured a quiet cove would be the\nperfect place to take a walk and calm\nboth our hearts and our minds.
You are truly a model Paladyn, Julietta.
Eeeeee! *cough* Er, I mean...\nI am nothing so special as all that.
I simply strive to consistently maintain\nproper Paladyn standards of behavior.
You focus on proper Paladyn behavior\neven amidst the frivolity of the shore.\nI could stand to learn from your example.
I fear I have become entranced by the\nbeauty of this place and forgotten myself.
Why, just now, my head is filled with\nsilly thoughts about how one might\ndiscover mermaids in this cove.
I wouldn't have taken you for a romantic.
W-well, as I said, it was a silly thought.\nAll this time at the beach must have\nunmoored my mind somewhat.
And there is nothing wrong with that!\nWe all need to allow ourselves the luxury\nof relaxation from time to time, no?
(I never would have imagined that Elly\nwould engage in such flights of fancy!)
(I'm so glad I brought her here and was\nable to witness this new, softer side.)
(Also, she said I was a model Paladyn,\nAND she seems more relaxed!)
A fiend is emerging from the sea!\nThat...that isn't supposed to happen!
We must take up arms and stop...\nOh, fie! We forgot our weapons!
Get to safety, Elisanne!\nI will deal with the beast!
No, it's too dangerous. We must fall back.
I will permit neither man nor beast\nto ruin your holiday!
You took it down in a single blow!\nSimply incredible...
Ha! That's what you get for trying\nto ruin the holiday of MY Elly!
It's in its death throes, Julietta! Look out!
She took the blow intended for me...\nAnd now the fiend is trying to\ndrag her underwater!
Stop right there, vile beast!\nYour reign of terror ends now!
I shall save you, Elly! Haaaaaaaaah!
*huff* *puff*  I managed to pull Elly\nfrom the fiend's grasp, but...
She won't wake up! What should I do?!
Okay, okay. Easy. You know what to do...
Hold on, Elly! I'll bring you back to life\nwith mouth-to-mouth resuscitation!
(Wait. But that means I have to...\nMy mouth... Hers... Us...)
(No! I couldn't possibly subject Elly\nto such a base affront!)
Okay. Okay, I'm going to do it.\nDeep breath...and...NOW.
N-no! Elisanne is DEFINITELY what I said.\nRegardless, are you all right?
A little water in the lungs, but...yes.\nI think I will be all right.
Oh, what a relief! I didn't know what\nto do when you wouldn't wake up!
I'm sorry, I must have worried you\nterribly for you to be studying me\nat such close proximity.

Y-yes, I was merely looking for signs of
life! CERTAINLY not on the verge of giving
you mouth-to-mouth! And besides, I didn't
save you, it was... Ummm...
A mermaid! Yes, that's it. A mermaid leapt\nfrom the ocean waves and saved you.
And that's that, so let's just go back and\nforget any of this ever happened!
